36#include "kuser_locl.h"
37
38static char *cache_str;
39static char *out_cache_str;
40static char *delegation_cred_str;
41static char *etype_str;
42static int transit_flag = 1;
43static int forwardable_flag;
44static int canonicalize_flag;
45static int is_hostbased_flag;
46static int is_canonical_flag;
47static char *impersonate_str;
48static char *nametype_str;
49static int store_flag = 1;
50static int cached_only_flag;
51static int debug_flag;
52static int version_flag;
53static int help_flag;
54
55struct getargs args[] = {
56 { "cache", 'c', arg_string, &cache_str,
57 NP_("credential cache to use", ""), "cache"},
58 { "out-cache", 0, arg_string, &out_cache_str,
59 NP_("credential cache to store credential in", ""), "cache"},
60 { "delegation-credential-cache",0,arg_string, &delegation_cred_str,
61 NP_("where to find the ticket use for delegation", ""), "cache"},
62 { "canonicalize", 0, arg_flag, &canonicalize_flag,
63 NP_("canonicalize the principal (chase referrals)", ""), NULL },
64 { "canonical", 0, arg_flag, &is_canonical_flag,
65 NP_("the name components are canonical", ""), NULL },
66 { "forwardable", 0, arg_flag, &forwardable_flag,
67 NP_("forwardable ticket requested", ""), NULL},
68 { "transit-check", 0, arg_negative_flag, &transit_flag, NULL, NULL },
69 { "enctype", 'e', arg_string, &etype_str,
70 NP_("encryption type to use", ""), "enctype"},
71 { "impersonate", 0, arg_string, &impersonate_str,
72 NP_("client to impersonate", ""), "principal"},
73 { "name-type", 0, arg_string, &nametype_str,
74 NP_("Kerberos name type", ""), NULL },
75 { "hostbased", 'H', arg_flag, &is_hostbased_flag,
76 NP_("indicate that the name is a host-based service name", ""), NULL },
77 { "store", 0, arg_negative_flag, &store_flag,
78 NP_("don't store the tickets obtained in the cache", ""), NULL },
79 { "cached-only", 0, arg_flag, &cached_only_flag,
80 NP_("don't talk to the KDC, just search the cache", ""), NULL },
81 { "debug", 0, arg_flag, &debug_flag, NULL, NULL },
82 { "version", 0, arg_flag, &version_flag, NULL, NULL },
83 { "help", 0, arg_flag, &help_flag, NULL, NULL }
84};
85
86static void
87usage(int ret)
88{
89 arg_printusage(args,
90 sizeof(args)/sizeof(*args),
91 NULL,
92 "service");
93 exit (ret);
94}
95
96int
97main(int argc, char **argv)
98{
99 krb5_error_code ret;
100 krb5_context context;
101 krb5_ccache cache;
102 krb5_creds *out;
103 int optidx = 0;
104 int32_t nametype = KRB5_NT_UNKNOWN;
105 krb5_get_creds_opt opt;
106 krb5_principal server = NULL;
107 krb5_principal impersonate;
108
109 setprogname(argv[0]);
110
111 ret = krb5_init_context(&context);
112 if (ret)
113 errx(1, "krb5_init_context failed: %d", ret);
114
115 if (getarg(args, sizeof(args) / sizeof(args[0]), argc, argv, &optidx))
116 usage(1);
117
118 if (help_flag)
119 usage (0);
120
121 if (version_flag) {
122 print_version(NULL);
123 exit(0);
124 }
125
126 argc -= optidx;
127 argv += optidx;
128
129 if (debug_flag) {
130 ret = krb5_set_debug_dest(context, getprogname(), "STDERR");
131 if (ret)
132 krb5_warn(context, ret, "krb5_set_debug_dest");
133 }
134
135 if (cache_str) {
136 ret = krb5_cc_resolve(context, cache_str, &cache);
137 if (ret)
138 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "%s", cache_str);
139 } else {
140 ret = krb5_cc_default (context, &cache);
141 if (ret)
142 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_cc_resolve");
143 }
144
145 ret = krb5_get_creds_opt_alloc(context, &opt);
146 if (ret)
147 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_get_creds_opt_alloc");
148
149 if (etype_str) {
150 krb5_enctype enctype;
151
152 ret = krb5_string_to_enctype(context, etype_str, &enctype);
153 if (ret)
154 krb5_errx(context, 1, N_("unrecognized enctype: %s", ""),
155 etype_str);
156 krb5_get_creds_opt_set_enctype(context, opt, enctype);
157 }
158
159 if (impersonate_str) {
160 ret = krb5_parse_name(context, impersonate_str, &impersonate);
161 if (ret)
162 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_parse_name %s", impersonate_str);
163 krb5_get_creds_opt_set_impersonate(context, opt, impersonate);
164 krb5_get_creds_opt_add_options(context, opt, KRB5_GC_NO_STORE);
165 krb5_free_principal(context, impersonate);
166 }
167
168 if (out_cache_str)
169 krb5_get_creds_opt_add_options(context, opt, KRB5_GC_NO_STORE);
170
171 if (forwardable_flag)
172 krb5_get_creds_opt_add_options(context, opt, KRB5_GC_FORWARDABLE);
173 if (!transit_flag)
174 krb5_get_creds_opt_add_options(context, opt, KRB5_GC_NO_TRANSIT_CHECK);
175 if (canonicalize_flag)
176 krb5_get_creds_opt_add_options(context, opt, KRB5_GC_CANONICALIZE);
177 if (!store_flag)
178 krb5_get_creds_opt_add_options(context, opt, KRB5_GC_NO_STORE);
179 if (cached_only_flag)
180 krb5_get_creds_opt_add_options(context, opt, KRB5_GC_CACHED);
181
182 if (delegation_cred_str) {
183 krb5_ccache id;
184 krb5_creds c, mc;
185 Ticket ticket;
186
187 krb5_cc_clear_mcred(&mc);
188 ret = krb5_cc_get_principal(context, cache, &mc.server);
189 if (ret)
190 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_cc_get_principal");
191
192 ret = krb5_cc_resolve(context, delegation_cred_str, &id);
193 if(ret)
194 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_cc_resolve");
195
196 ret = krb5_cc_retrieve_cred(context, id, 0, &mc, &c);
197 if(ret)
198 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_cc_retrieve_cred");
199
200 ret = decode_Ticket(c.ticket.data, c.ticket.length, &ticket, NULL);
201 if (ret) {
202 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
203 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "decode_Ticket");
204 }
205 krb5_free_cred_contents(context, &c);
206
207 ret = krb5_get_creds_opt_set_ticket(context, opt, &ticket);
208 if(ret)
209 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_get_creds_opt_set_ticket");
210 free_Ticket(&ticket);
211
212 krb5_cc_close(context, id);
213 krb5_free_principal(context, mc.server);
214
215 krb5_get_creds_opt_add_options(context, opt,
216 KRB5_GC_CONSTRAINED_DELEGATION);
217 }
218
219 if (nametype_str != NULL) {
220 ret = krb5_parse_nametype(context, nametype_str, &nametype);
221 if (ret)
222 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_parse_nametype");
223 }
224
225 if (nametype == KRB5_NT_SRV_HST ||
226 nametype == KRB5_NT_SRV_HST_NEEDS_CANON)
227 is_hostbased_flag = 1;
228
229 if (is_hostbased_flag) {
230 const char *sname = NULL;
231 const char *hname = NULL;
232
233 if (nametype_str != NULL &&
234 nametype != KRB5_NT_SRV_HST &&
235 nametype != KRB5_NT_SRV_HST_NEEDS_CANON)
236 krb5_errx(context, 1, "--hostbased not compatible with "
237 "non-hostbased --name-type");
238
239 if (is_canonical_flag)
240 nametype = KRB5_NT_SRV_HST;
241 else
242 nametype = KRB5_NT_SRV_HST_NEEDS_CANON;
243
244 /*
245 * Host-based service names can have more than one component.
246 *
247 * RFC5179 did not, but should have, assign a Kerberos name-type
248 * corresponding to GSS_C_NT_DOMAINBASED. But it's basically a
249 * host-based service name type with one additional component.
250 *
251 * So that's how we're treating host-based service names here:
252 * two or more components.
253 */
254
255 if (argc == 0) {
256 usage(1);
257 } else if (argc == 1) {
258 krb5_principal server2;
259
260 /*
261 * In this case the one argument is a principal name, not the
262 * service name.
263 *
264 * We parse the argument as a principal name, extract the service
265 * and hostname components, use krb5_sname_to_principal(), then
266 * extract the service and hostname components from that.
267 */
268
269 ret = krb5_parse_name(context, argv[0], &server);
270 if (ret)
271 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_parse_name %s", argv[0]);
272 sname = krb5_principal_get_comp_string(context, server, 0);
273
274 /*
275 * If a single-component principal name is given, then we'll
276 * default the hostname, as krb5_principal_get_comp_string()
277 * returns NULL in this case.
278 */
279 hname = krb5_principal_get_comp_string(context, server, 1);
280
281 ret = krb5_sname_to_principal(context, hname, sname,
282 KRB5_NT_SRV_HST, &server2);
283 sname = krb5_principal_get_comp_string(context, server2, 0);
284 hname = krb5_principal_get_comp_string(context, server2, 1);
285
286 /*
287 * Modify the original with the new sname/hname. This way we
288 * retain any additional principal name components from the given
289 * principal name.
290 *
291 * The name-type is set further below.
292 */
293 ret = krb5_principal_set_comp_string(context, server, 0, sname);
294 if (ret)
295 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_principal_set_comp_string %s", argv[0]);
296 ret = krb5_principal_set_comp_string(context, server, 1, hname);
297 if (ret)
298 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_principal_set_comp_string %s", argv[0]);
299 krb5_free_principal(context, server2);
300 } else {
301 size_t i;
302
303 /*
304 * In this case the arguments are principal name components.
305 *
306 * The service and hostname components can be defaulted by passing
307 * empty strings.
308 */
309 sname = argv[0];
310 if (*sname == '\0')
311 sname = NULL;
312 hname = argv[1];
313 if (hname == NULL || *hname == '\0')
314 hname = NULL;
315 ret = krb5_sname_to_principal(context, hname, sname,
316 KRB5_NT_SRV_HST, &server);
317 if (ret)
318 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_sname_to_principal");
319
320 for (i = 2; i < argc; i++) {
321 ret = krb5_principal_set_comp_string(context, server, i, argv[i]);
322 if (ret)
323 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_principal_set_comp_string");
324 }
325 }
326 } else if (argc == 1) {
327 ret = krb5_parse_name(context, argv[0], &server);
328 if (ret)
329 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_parse_name %s", argv[0]);
330 } else {
331 usage(1);
332 }
333
334 if (nametype != KRB5_NT_UNKNOWN)
335 server->name.name_type = (NAME_TYPE)nametype;
336
337 ret = krb5_get_creds(context, opt, cache, server, &out);
338 if (ret)
339 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_get_creds");
340
341 if (out_cache_str) {
342 krb5_ccache id;
343
344 ret = krb5_cc_resolve(context, out_cache_str, &id);
345 if(ret)
346 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_cc_resolve");
347
348 ret = krb5_cc_initialize(context, id, out->client);
349 if(ret)
350 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_cc_initialize");
351
352 ret = krb5_cc_store_cred(context, id, out);
353 if(ret)
354 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "krb5_cc_store_cred");
355 krb5_cc_close(context, id);
356 }
357
358 krb5_free_creds(context, out);
359 krb5_free_principal(context, server);
360 krb5_get_creds_opt_free(context, opt);
361 krb5_cc_close (context, cache);
362 krb5_free_context (context);
363
364 return 0;
365}
